 SUPABASE_URL=your-supabase-project-url
 SUPABASE_KEY=your-service-role-api-key
 DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres.[PROJECT_REF]:[DB_PASSWORD]@[REGION].pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres


# Suggested .env.example values + how to get them from Supabase
# You can keep .env.example like this, but add comments explaining each value:

# SUPABASE_URL=your-supabase-project-urlSUPABASE_KEY=your-service-role-api-keyDATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres.[PROJECT_REF]:[DB_PASSWORD]@[REGION].pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgresSUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD=your-database-password
# How to get each value from Supabase
# SUPABASE_URL (project URL)
# Go to the Supabase dashboard.
# Open your project.
# In the left sidebar, click Settings → API.
# Copy the Project URL (e.g. https://xyzcompany.supabase.co).
# SUPABASE_KEY (service role key)
# Same page: Settings → API.
# Under Project API keys, find service_role.
# Copy the Service Role key and paste it as SUPABASE_KEY.
# Keep this secret; never commit .env.
# SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD (database password)
# Go to Settings → Database.
# Under Connection Info (or Connection string), you’ll see the database password or a “Reset password” button.
# Use that password as SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD.
# DATABASE_URL (Postgres connection string via pooler)
# In Settings → Database, find Connection string.
# Choose URI and then Pooled (recommended for web apps).
# Copy the full postgresql://... string and paste it as DATABASE_URL.
